<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Roast2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Roast,</orth> vb. to dress or cook by exposure to the fire: <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.935" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 935</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.48" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 48</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.498" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 498</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.361" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 361</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 2.3.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 3, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 5.2.279" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. V, 2, 279</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.2.183" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 2, 183</bibl>. (Pyrrhus) <cit><quote>baked and impasted with the parching streets, . . . --ed in wrath and fire,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.483" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 483</bibl></cit>.
